DDL - data defination language 

data existance 

Alter command -> DDL

1. ADD columns in exist table

syntax ->  ALTER TABLE <table_name> ADD col_name datatype;

example :- ALTER table students ADD createdAt datetime;


2. Drop column from exist table

syntax -> ALTER TABLE <table_name> DROP COLUMN <column_name>; 


3. To Update Modify the exist table

syntax -> ALTER TABLE <table_name> MODIFY COLUMN <column_name> datetype;

example:- ALTER TABLE students MODIFY COLUMN year year;



DQL - data query language

to retrive data 

SELECT -> read from table

simple ,basic syntax ->  select * from <table_name> 

advance syntax -> select col_name1,col_name_2,col_name3 from table;






DML - Data manipulation language

already existance action perform 

table data insert, update, delete


INSERT

simple insert 

syntax ->  INSERT INTO <table_name> values("col_1",col_2,"col_3",......"upto nth col");

advance -> INSERT INTO <table_name>(sid,name) values("value1",value);



Constraints


1. NOT NULL

syntax -> create table students(sid int not null,name varchar(30) not null,branch enum("cse","civil","me","iot"),age tinyInt,year char(4));


2 Default 

syntax -> create table students(sid int not null,name varchar(30) not null,branch enum("cse","civil","me","iot"),age tinyInt,year year default 2024);





